name: How Much Can You Carry by Floriane de Lassée

metadata.description: Putrie, Toraja Country, Sulawesia, Indonesia, 2013. Whenever an ancestor dies, a buffalo is killed and its horns are hung on the pediment of the family home. The wealth of a family is both measured by the number of animals it posesses and its ancestral line, visible through this stack of horns. This little girl carries a heavy legacy.
metadata.name: Putrie
